The paper deals with person re-identification using generative adversarial networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach using adversarial learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
